cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new neural architecture for deep learning that focuses on improving performance in image classification and object detection tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the integration of grammar models and deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of phrase structure grammar and dependency grammar, which are topics in natural language processing, falling under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for adversarial defense, which is a topic in neural networks and falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
